CSV Export Instructions

For each screenshot:  
- Save a CSV file with the same name as the image, but with a .csv extension.  
- CSV columns:  
  - Text: (German sentence).
  - Sound: (leave empty)
  - Back Extra: (German sentence). 
  - Hint: (English sentence) and "<br>(card generated with help of ChatGPT)"  
  - screenshot or image (PGM): Include the HTML tag that links the screenshot JPG file so it can be imported into Anki.  
  - Tags separated by single space: a tag starting with date extracted from the filename in format YYYY.MM.DD:: followed by time in format HHMMSS extracted from the screenshot filename (usually 6 characters from 21 to 26), another tag which is the current date in the format YYYY.MM.DD, a tag called no_pronunciation, and "clozeDeletion"
- Do not include a header row in the CSV file.  
- Also display the generated cards on screen.  
